WEBVTT

00:18.810 --> 00:19.800
Hey, Larry?

00:21.480 --> 00:22.595
Larry, are you OK?

00:28.570 --> 00:30.186
He doesn't need you.

00:46.630 --> 00:47.916
Hey, Loomis.

00:48.210 --> 00:49.416
I heard something.

00:50.420 --> 00:52.081
Heard your mother wears army boots.

00:52.210 --> 00:53.917
-She'll do it with anybody.
-Shut up.

00:54.050 --> 00:56.712
My ma said she saw her
and Mr. Smith eating at Nino's.

00:57.140 --> 01:00.258
Said she was laughing like a hyena
and touching him all over.

01:00.390 --> 01:01.710
Said it was disgusting.

01:05.770 --> 01:08.307
-Now you're gonna get it.
-But I'm going down swinging.

01:17.200 --> 01:20.522
There was a boy

01:22.370 --> 01:26.739
A very strange, enchanted boy

01:27.540 --> 01:31.829
They say he wandered very far...

01:32.880 --> 01:34.086
We're going to London.

01:35.930 --> 01:37.637
Hi, Wally. Can I talk to my mom?

01:39.260 --> 01:42.218
I'd prefer it if you addressed me
by the title of the office, Larry.

01:43.850 --> 01:45.727
Oh, dearest Sovereign Protector--

01:45.850 --> 01:46.840
Larry!

01:47.850 --> 01:50.649
-I'm sorry. He's been like this.
-It's OK.

01:51.980 --> 01:55.143
He who thinks a fire... is a fire.

01:56.200 --> 01:57.235
Remember that.

01:57.360 --> 01:58.486
Screw you.

02:00.120 --> 02:01.110
Larry.

02:04.410 --> 02:05.866
Mr. Smith and I?

02:06.290 --> 02:08.327
Larry, that's ridiculous.

02:08.460 --> 02:09.949
Don't listen to rumors.

02:10.419 --> 02:13.412
-Just because we're going to London--
-Wait, wait, wait!

02:13.960 --> 02:14.950
London?

02:15.380 --> 02:18.179
-What the hell?
-I just found out myself.

02:18.680 --> 02:21.468
-We're leaving tonight.
-Mom, what about his wife?

02:21.600 --> 02:24.763
Linnie understands. You will, too.

02:25.140 --> 02:29.896
The Sovereign Protector
needs my help.

02:30.020 --> 02:31.647
Mom, he does dry-cleaning.

02:35.280 --> 02:37.146
I wish I could tell you everything.

02:37.950 --> 02:39.987
It would make this so much easier.

02:40.110 --> 02:42.192
You're gonna leave me alone
in the apartment?

02:42.320 --> 02:44.288
You're old enough
to take care of yourself.

02:44.620 --> 02:47.328
If you need anything,
come to the Lodge.

02:47.870 --> 02:49.497
The knights will help you.

02:49.870 --> 02:51.452
Mom, don't go. He doesn't need you.

02:51.580 --> 02:53.332
Why do you believe
everything he says?

02:56.050 --> 02:57.916
Go pig out on some turkey.

02:58.220 --> 03:00.621
Be thankful, Larry.

03:01.640 --> 03:03.347
Be thankful.

03:09.390 --> 03:10.972
It's omelet time.

03:11.100 --> 03:12.261
Oh, yeah.

03:13.690 --> 03:15.101
The Larry Special.

03:16.610 --> 03:18.271
I hope you guys are hungry.

03:25.950 --> 03:26.781
Damn it.

03:28.120 --> 03:29.110
Oh, well.

03:29.960 --> 03:32.281
We'll just have to make
our rations last.

03:33.460 --> 03:35.531
We need to talk about last night.

03:35.670 --> 03:36.990
Yeah, yeah, yeah. I'm OK.

03:37.130 --> 03:38.507
Too many vodka stingers.

03:39.090 --> 03:40.376
It happens. I'm fine.

03:40.510 --> 03:42.421
You were walking around naked.

03:42.930 --> 03:45.501
Yeah. Hilarious, wasn't it?

03:47.060 --> 03:50.303
So, what are people saying
about my junk?

03:54.270 --> 03:57.353
People were just really worried
about you last night, Lar.

03:57.780 --> 03:59.930
You know,
not about your junk, per se, but--

04:00.070 --> 04:01.060
Larry...

04:01.820 --> 04:04.232
Something's wrong. You need rest.

04:05.320 --> 04:07.368
Maybe you can stay
at my place for a while.

04:07.490 --> 04:10.869
Yeah. I can sort of... I can sort of
trailer-sit for a while.

04:11.000 --> 04:12.206
It's perfect timing.

04:12.330 --> 04:15.209
My sister just kind of
evicted me last night.

04:15.330 --> 04:16.331
Why?

04:17.089 --> 04:19.240
Oh, there's no... no real reason.

04:19.380 --> 04:21.007
Just money, you know?

04:22.800 --> 04:24.677
But, yeah, I start a new temp job.

04:24.800 --> 04:28.179
It's graveyard,
so I can crash here all day.

04:28.680 --> 04:31.763
You know, sort of be caretaker
for the property, you know?

04:31.890 --> 04:34.188
This property doesn't exist.

04:37.060 --> 04:38.061
OK.

04:38.980 --> 04:39.970
Well...

04:41.150 --> 04:42.640
I need to get on the road.

04:43.150 --> 04:44.606
But I can come by tonight.

04:45.450 --> 04:47.020
Keep an eye on him this afternoon?

04:47.160 --> 04:48.275
Hey, hey, hey.

04:48.410 --> 04:50.651
Stop talking about me
like I'm not here.

04:51.620 --> 04:53.031
I'm doing fine on my own.

04:58.340 --> 04:59.375
Shit! Fire!

05:33.500 --> 05:36.618
You said you were seeing
a shadow or something?

05:37.750 --> 05:38.820
I saw...

05:44.130 --> 05:45.336
I don't know what I saw.

05:46.010 --> 05:47.375
Let's cover your left eye.

05:48.140 --> 05:50.347
Try reading the bottom line.

05:51.470 --> 05:52.710
X, V...

05:53.600 --> 05:57.264
<i>N, ARGW, AL.</i>

05:58.020 --> 05:59.476
OK. That's good enough.

06:03.650 --> 06:07.609
You should just open a business where
people get to come into a dark room

06:07.740 --> 06:09.902
and answer simple questions.

06:10.030 --> 06:11.862
That is a great idea.

06:15.660 --> 06:17.537
Do people ever tell you
their secrets?

06:17.660 --> 06:18.661
All the time.

06:21.670 --> 06:22.660
Like...

06:24.170 --> 06:25.160
"Doctor...

06:26.010 --> 06:30.129
I've been having an affair,
and the guy doesn't even know

06:30.260 --> 06:32.638
I have what's apparently
a terminal illness"?

06:34.220 --> 06:35.802
No. No, nothing that dark.

06:40.730 --> 06:42.607
Good news. Your eyes are fine.

06:44.980 --> 06:45.970
I know.

06:47.530 --> 06:48.941
What do you know about Captain?

06:49.320 --> 06:52.062
I've got a theory about Captain.
He's not a real guy.

06:52.570 --> 06:55.483
Serious. Think about it.
No one's ever met him.

06:55.620 --> 06:57.361
He's just a line item
on a spreadsheet

06:57.500 --> 06:59.707
for some heavy dudes
we'll never know.

07:00.540 --> 07:02.201
Captain's a tax write-off.

07:02.710 --> 07:05.247
He's the shadow of the dream
that never was.

07:05.380 --> 07:07.451
No, Captain's real. I met him.

07:07.590 --> 07:09.297
-What does he look like?
-He's white.

07:09.420 --> 07:10.876
No shit! What else?

07:11.010 --> 07:13.843
Man, I don't know!
He's a white-looking white dude.

07:13.970 --> 07:15.961
They say he's somewhere
in the desert now.

07:16.810 --> 07:17.675
Captain?

07:17.810 --> 07:19.471
His Orbis deal is really happening.

07:19.600 --> 07:21.477
I heard
City Hall approved it last week.

07:23.520 --> 07:24.817
This is blackmail!

07:28.490 --> 07:30.276
It's my money. I earned it.

07:34.990 --> 07:36.367
You're such an asshole!

07:36.830 --> 07:39.288
I pay the bill.
I get to be the asshole!

07:39.410 --> 07:40.400
Exactly.

07:40.540 --> 07:42.668
You need to think about your future.

07:42.790 --> 07:44.838
Or do you want to be
like Dud and Liz?

07:46.750 --> 07:48.798
Oh, Liz, I'm sorry.

07:50.010 --> 07:51.421
No, you're right.

07:51.550 --> 07:54.508
I am the ghost
of your Shamroxx future, Alice.

07:55.180 --> 07:56.170
Beware.

07:59.060 --> 08:01.381
Ernie, I owe you an apology.

08:01.520 --> 08:02.760
That's right, bitch.

08:03.940 --> 08:07.319
I am 100% your bitch.

08:07.440 --> 08:09.602
I didn't believe you,
but here you are,

08:09.740 --> 08:11.560
ten steps ahead of everybody.

08:11.700 --> 08:14.988
The City Council, those billboards.

08:15.120 --> 08:17.691
"Is there another way to live?"
What does that even mean?

08:17.830 --> 08:20.492
I don't know, I don't care.

08:20.620 --> 08:23.282
And now you've got Captain
in the crosshairs!

08:23.420 --> 08:26.629
I am going to need
a serious expense account,

08:26.750 --> 08:30.209
so when I get to the desert
I don't look like a chump.

08:30.340 --> 08:31.910
Done and done.

08:32.380 --> 08:34.371
OK, we've got a couple more
little things.

08:35.260 --> 08:39.299
Irv Sendero
is out from Ohio next week.

08:39.429 --> 08:42.342
Your basic factory-guy jerk-off.

08:42.480 --> 08:44.847
I've set up tee times in El Dorado.

08:44.980 --> 08:48.189
Ernie, I promised him
that you would shepherd him around.

08:48.320 --> 08:50.470
-I can't. I'm going to the desert.
-What?

08:51.280 --> 08:52.099
Captain.

08:52.990 --> 08:55.857
Oh, you're right.
A little scheduling conflict.

08:58.240 --> 09:00.732
Beautiful Jeff,
how about I send you after Captain?

09:00.870 --> 09:02.326
What? No.

09:02.450 --> 09:03.781
I'd absolutely love to, Bob.

09:03.910 --> 09:07.699
Ernie, I promised Irv
that you would be his guy this trip.

09:07.830 --> 09:08.877
He loves you,

09:09.000 --> 09:12.300
and you're the only guy on the planet
who's a worse golfer than he is.

09:12.420 --> 09:13.660
You make him look good!

09:13.800 --> 09:16.713
Screw Irv!
Let Beautiful Jeff jerk him off!

09:16.840 --> 09:20.094
Well, look, here's the problem,
Ernie - I'm a scratch golfer.

09:20.220 --> 09:21.301
I can't help it.

09:21.430 --> 09:24.559
My natural stroke
is just so... smooth.

09:24.690 --> 09:26.727
-I love watching you hit.
-No!

09:27.770 --> 09:30.478
He'll never find Captain.
This is my thing.

09:30.610 --> 09:32.146
Ernie, you're off this.

09:32.280 --> 09:34.351
Stick to what you do best,

09:34.490 --> 09:36.857
and don't begrudge
another man his gifts.

09:36.990 --> 09:37.809
Understand?

09:45.370 --> 09:46.781
Just here to grab my stuff.

09:49.790 --> 09:50.780
Sure.

10:03.930 --> 10:07.889
Hey, can we talk,
in reasonable tones?

10:09.350 --> 10:10.351
Yeah.

10:11.900 --> 10:12.890
Of course.

10:13.030 --> 10:15.351
We're both sophisticated adults.

10:21.070 --> 10:22.697
I'm sorry about your foot.

10:22.830 --> 10:25.151
That's OK. It's seen worse.

10:28.000 --> 10:33.450
And I'm sorry
for escalating the situation.

10:35.090 --> 10:36.296
Where are you staying?

10:36.880 --> 10:38.041
With Larry Loomis,

10:38.180 --> 10:39.625
our Sovereign Protector.

10:40.140 --> 10:43.383
He's got some property down by
the Lodge. It's a pretty nice setup.

10:44.430 --> 10:45.761
"Sovereign Protector"?

10:46.850 --> 10:49.842
God, you're really all-in
on this Mason stuff, huh?

10:49.980 --> 10:51.300
Yeah, yeah.

10:51.440 --> 10:52.430
Except...

10:53.320 --> 10:54.640
we're the Lynx.

10:54.780 --> 10:56.270
Yeah, not the Masons.

10:56.400 --> 11:00.280
The Masons were wannabe Rosicrucians,
and Rosicrucians were a hoax

11:00.410 --> 11:02.868
that pretty much
just got out of hand.

11:02.990 --> 11:05.118
There's a great essay
by this British junkie--

11:05.240 --> 11:06.696
I'm worried about you, Sean.

11:07.200 --> 11:10.454
OK, Elizabeth serious-full-name.

11:11.630 --> 11:13.951
If Dad were here,
he'd be worried about you, too.

11:17.800 --> 11:19.165
Except he's not.

11:20.300 --> 11:23.793
Because, according to you,
Dad killed himself.

11:26.060 --> 11:31.226
Do... Do you hear how insane
that even sounds?

11:32.020 --> 11:34.307
Dud, you can't start to move on

11:34.440 --> 11:36.852
until you admit
that bad stuff has happened.

11:36.980 --> 11:38.311
I know that's hard for you.

11:38.440 --> 11:40.943
It was hard for me,
but I faced up to it.

11:42.240 --> 11:43.230
But...

11:44.740 --> 11:47.038
you've always been
afraid of the dark.

11:50.120 --> 11:51.861
Who's not afraid of the dark, Liz?

11:52.420 --> 11:55.128
At least it makes sense.
You know what doesn't make sense?

11:57.170 --> 11:58.547
Being afraid of the light.

12:00.720 --> 12:05.794
You're happy
inside your dark little witch-cave.

12:09.890 --> 12:11.130
I'm sorry, I'm not.

12:12.350 --> 12:13.897
I'm not gonna live there with you.

12:25.070 --> 12:26.617
I'm on the right path, Liz.

12:29.540 --> 12:30.860
I'm gonna prove it to you.

12:38.380 --> 12:41.668
He's embarrassed about what happened,
he just can't admit it.

12:42.090 --> 12:45.754
Well, Larry shouldn't be embarrassed.
He's got a magnificent set of balls.

12:46.300 --> 12:47.347
Yeah.

12:48.310 --> 12:50.176
He seemed so scared and frail.

12:50.310 --> 12:52.381
I mean, it just broke my heart.

12:52.520 --> 12:55.342
He's still Larry.
He just needs to slow down a little.

12:55.480 --> 12:58.518
I'm gonna try to get him
over to my place for a few nights.

12:58.820 --> 13:01.027
Yeah. You should have seen him
this morning.

13:01.150 --> 13:04.700
He was all piss and vinegar, even
after he burned off his eyebrows.

13:05.110 --> 13:06.100
What?

13:06.240 --> 13:08.652
No, he's fine.
He just looks a little crazy, so...

13:10.950 --> 13:13.783
OK, I'm sorry,
but this is a wake-up call.

13:14.750 --> 13:16.240
Larry can't be on his own any more.

13:16.370 --> 13:18.452
He needs to transition
into assisted living.

13:18.590 --> 13:21.412
-You want to put him in a home?
-Come on, Ernie.

13:21.550 --> 13:24.838
You can't pretend things are getting
better when they're getting worse.

13:25.970 --> 13:28.883
Now, look, Larry deserves
the best care possible,

13:29.010 --> 13:31.308
and I don't think any of us
can give it to him.

13:36.650 --> 13:37.640
OK.

13:38.100 --> 13:39.807
I'll talk to him.

13:43.400 --> 13:46.062
Obviously, the succession
will have to be reconsidered.

13:46.200 --> 13:47.770
This is what's on your mind now?

13:47.910 --> 13:49.196
I'm just saying!

13:49.620 --> 13:51.486
Somebody from London
will be here soon.

13:51.620 --> 13:54.282
-We can let them sort it all out.
-I can't wait for London.

13:54.410 --> 13:56.788
These emissaries have
the coolest gig ever.

13:56.920 --> 13:58.957
They live like rock stars.

14:00.380 --> 14:02.587
Mum, Dad, I'm leaving.

14:06.010 --> 14:07.717
I'm going now!

14:10.550 --> 14:11.881
To California.

14:12.720 --> 14:14.017
I've told you a million...

14:20.650 --> 14:21.970
This is the endgame.

14:23.020 --> 14:25.899
The corporate-industrial dragon
has poisoned itself,

14:26.030 --> 14:28.237
gorging on the flesh of its workers,

14:28.360 --> 14:30.522
leaving the vultures
to pick the bones.

14:30.990 --> 14:32.276
That's a bummer.

14:32.410 --> 14:34.037
Que sera, bro.

14:34.160 --> 14:35.616
You can't turn back time.

14:36.120 --> 14:38.452
-This is where we are.
-Yeah.

14:38.580 --> 14:41.834
So, you work all day at Shamroxx,
and then you work all night here?

14:41.960 --> 14:44.088
-When do you sleep?
-I don't sleep.

14:44.590 --> 14:46.376
We're all gonna be
replaced by robots,

14:46.510 --> 14:50.048
so the only way to survive
is to become a robot.

14:52.470 --> 14:56.634
You know, I never really saw myself
working in law enforcement,

14:56.770 --> 14:59.057
but, I've got to say,
I kind of dig the uniform.

14:59.190 --> 15:00.430
It's all theater.

15:01.440 --> 15:02.430
What do you mean?

15:03.320 --> 15:06.062
I mean don't take any dumb risks.

15:06.190 --> 15:09.069
You see or hear anything,

15:09.200 --> 15:10.349
run the other way.

15:11.160 --> 15:14.778
